s research process involves a well defined meeting structure to develop consensus on all ideas each investment style is directed by a style portfolio manager who drives the decision making of their respective portfolios all members of the portfolio team portfolio managers and analysts are responsible for maintenance research and idea generation within their areas of expertise research responsibilities are divided by sector portfolio managers and analysts conduct a complete capital structure analysis® on the companies they follow identify the best relative value within the capital structure debt or equity and bring their ideas to the team for consideration the best of those ideas are reviewed by the style portfolio manager who evaluates how to apply those that closely align with core business strategies richard hocker founder chief investment officer  chief executive officer mr hocker founded penn capital in  and serves as chief investment officer  chief executive officer guiding overall portfolio strategy  his investing and institutional noninvestment grade corporate lending experience spans over forty years while serving as a partner for delaware investment advisors dia from  to  he was responsible for building the investment side of dia’s fixed income operation  during this period mr hocker developed and managed one of the nation’s first high yield mutual funds the delchester high yield bond fund he also served as the first high yield bond manager for a number of institutional clients including general motors state of vermont teachers retirement association and colorado fire and police  prior to dia mr hocker trained as a corporate lender and supported key senior lenders at provident national bank which is now pnc a top  us banking institution  he later rose to serve as head of the investment division  mr hocker also founded and served as ceo of covenant bank a nj based regional bank which grew to  branches and mm in deposits before being acquired by wachovia corporation in  he and his wife marcia hocker are the founders of the ethel mae hocker foundation the ethel mae hocker foundation provides educational opportunities to less fortunate deserving greater philadelphiaarea elementary and high school students mr hocker received both his bs in accounting and mba in finance from the kogod school of business at american university eric green cfa senior managing partner director of research senior portfolio manager mr green began his career at penn capital in july  prior to joining penn capital he gained experience with the federal national mortgage association the royal bank of scotland and the united states securities and exchange commission where he served as a financial analyst in the division of investment management as director of research mr green is responsible for guiding the firm’s day to day research process he also serves as the portfolio manager for penn capital’s small cap and mid cap equity strategies and chairs penn capital’s equity strategy committee mr green is also a member of the board of directors and the executive committee of the adl midatlantic region he received a bsba cum laude from american university and received an mba from the yale school of management scott schumacher senior managing partner senior portfolio manager mr schumacher began his career with penn capital in  he is responsible for global oversight of all equity and high yield trading mr schumacher is a member of the firm’s credit strategy committee and the firm’s executive committee which drives overall strategy and management of the firm he received a bs in accounting from rutgers university j paulo silva cfa managing partner senior portfolio manager mr silva began his career with penn capital in  as a research analyst focused on technology and industrial companies in addition mr silva has focused on a number of distressed debt situations successfully completing a reorganization through serving on the official committee of creditors today 